name: Alabama

character_formatting.stack_position: Various positions depending on plate type

notes: Alabama does NOT allow the use of the letter 'O'. The number '0' must always be used. Vertical characters must be entered as seen. Do not key 3 character verticals. On current standard plates, the registration begins with a 1 or 2 number county code. PROCESSING: Always uses standard processing regardless of plate type.

processing_metadata.description: Official Alabama DMV processing rules and validation requirements

global_rules.character_restrictions: Does not allow the use of the letter 'O'. The number '0' must always be used. Vertical characters must be entered as seen.
global_rules.code_system: All plate types use Code Number 0
global_rules.county_coding: Current standard plates begin with 1 or 2 number county code
global_rules.vertical_handling: Do not key 3 character verticals - omit them from processing
global_rules.omit_characters: 3 character vertical stacks - do not include in processing
